main event: Civilians sighted several silvery-white objects in the sky following white lights around in Santa Fe, New Mexico in November 1957.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 3 hours.
There were 9 objects spotted in the sky.
The report mentions conflicting research in the files regarding what was sighted.
The report lists the conclusions as 'Probably Balloons, Possibly Aircraft, Possibly Astronomical, Unknown'.
The report mentions that there were no photographs taken of the sighting.
sighted object: several silvery-white objects following white lights
